The paper is about using deep learning techniques for fine-grained image analysis, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning algorithms, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the application of AI techniques, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also covers image retrieval, which is related to information retrieval and falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses benchmark datasets and domain-specific applications, which are related to multimedia and falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
